text:
Linked to : Arsenal, Tottenham , Liverpool 
THIERRY HENRY waxed lyrical over Mbappe’s potential in his new column earlier this week – and predictably everyone is labelling him the new Henry. 
The 18-year-old has often come off the bench this season, in much the same way Monaco used a young(er) Anthony Martial, but stole the spotlight with a hat-trick against Metz earlier this month. 
Arsene Wenger has already admitted that Arsenal are hot on the teenager’s heels – there seems to be a committed drive from the Emirates to snap him up before long.
